---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Teachers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Teachers working internationally, covering teaching positions abroad, education careers, and global teaching opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Teachers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Teachers working abroad, educating students internationally, and pursuing careers across international schools and education systems worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/teacher-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/teacher-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Teacher Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Teachers educate students, develop curriculum, assess learning, and shape young minds. International teaching offers opportunities to work in diverse educational systems, experience different pedagogical approaches, and develop expertise across global education contexts.
      </p>
      <p>
        International teaching opportunities exist through international schools, language institutes, education programs, and schools actively recruiting overseas teachers.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Teachers working abroad across international schools and education systems worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Teachers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Voice care', why: 'Teaching demands voice use', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Student challenges and burnout', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Infectious disease', why: 'Classroom exposure', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Wellness support', why: 'Work-life balance', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Standing and desk work', typical: 'Consider including' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Voice and Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Teachers use their voices extensively—lecturing, leading discussions, managing classrooms. Voice strain is a real occupational hazard. Teachers also stand for extended periods and move throughout classrooms. These physical demands benefit from appropriate coverage.
      </p>
      <p>
        Voice care and ergonomic support address the physical realities of classroom teaching.
      </p>

      <h3>Emotional Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Teaching involves emotional investment in student success, managing challenging behaviors, and navigating parent relationships. Teacher burnout is increasingly recognized as a significant concern. International teaching adds cultural adjustment and distance from support systems.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>International School</h3>
      <p>
        Established international school. Comprehensive benefits. Expatriate community. International schools offer quality.
      </p>

      <h3>Private School</h3>
      <p>
        Local private institution. Benefits vary. Cultural immersion. Private schools offer variety.
      </p>

      <h3>Language Institute</h3>
      <p>
        ESL or language school. Often basic benefits. Language focus. Institutes offer entry point.
      </p>

      <h3>Public School</h3>
      <p>
        Government school placement. Government benefits. Local integration. Public offers authenticity.
      </p>

      <h3>Online Teaching</h3>
      <p>
        Virtual instruction. Self-provided coverage. Location flexibility. Online offers freedom.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Teachers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Teachers working abroad across international schools and education systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Teacher Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Teaching License</h3>
      <p>
        Home country teaching credential. State or national license. Certification status. License often required.
      </p>

      <h3>Education Degree</h3>
      <p>
        Bachelor's in education or subject area. Teaching qualification. Degree verification. Degree typically required.
      </p>

      <h3>Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Classroom teaching years. Grade level experience. Subject expertise. Experience valued highly.
      </p>

      <h3>TEFL/TESOL</h3>
      <p>
        English teaching certification. ESL qualification. Language teaching credential. TEFL opens doors.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Voice Strain</h3>
      <p>
        Lecturing demands. Classroom projection. Daily voice use. Voice care important.
      </p>

      <h3>Classroom Exposure</h3>
      <p>
        Student illness. Shared spaces. Seasonal illness. Infectious disease coverage valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Burnout Risk</h3>
      <p>
        Emotional investment. Workload demands. Parent interactions. Mental health support essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Physical Activity</h3>
      <p>
        Standing teaching. Classroom movement. Activity supervision. Ergonomic coverage helpful.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Instruction</h3>
      <p>
        Lesson delivery. Student engagement. Differentiated teaching. Instruction creates learning.
      </p>

      <h3>Planning</h3>
      <p>
        Curriculum development. Lesson preparation. Resource creation. Planning enables instruction.
      </p>

      <h3>Assessment</h3>
      <p>
        Student evaluation. Grade management. Progress reporting. Assessment guides learning.
      </p>

      <h3>Community</h3>
      <p>
        Parent communication. Colleague collaboration. School involvement. Community builds support.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Strong Demand</h3>
      <p>
        International schools growing. English teachers needed. STEM teachers valued. Demand strong.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Lead Teacher. Department Head. Curriculum Coordinator. Principal. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        Teaching skills universal. Credentials specific. IB training valued. Core skills transfer.
      </p>

      <h3>Field Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        EdTech integration. Hybrid learning. Global curricula. Field evolving continuously.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a teacher considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            International schools typically provide benefits. Credentials matter. Experience valued. Cultural adjustment expected.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Quality international schools yes. Language institutes vary significantly. Verify coverage carefully. School quality correlates.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is burnout a significant concern?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes in teaching. Emotional demands real. Cultural adjustment adds stress. Mental health support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do teaching credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Teaching skills yes. Credentials vary. International school standards exist. Core competence transfers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is voice strain a real concern?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for teachers. Daily voice use demanding. Prevention important. Voice care coverage valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            International education growing. Qualified teachers needed. Opportunities expanding. Outlook positive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating employer benefits packages. Prioritize mental health support for emotional demands. Consider voice care coverage for classroom teaching. Verify infectious disease coverage for school environments.
      </p>
      <p>
        Teachers shape future generations worldwide. Your coverage should support teaching careers—addressing voice and emotional demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across education work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Teaching Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Teachers working abroad across international schools and education systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
